hives    Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Breadcrumbs    Home    Help     Print, scan and copy   Printing, scanning and copying are available at all library locations.  printers print printing scanners scanning copying      Chicago  Copiers/scanners are available at both Chicago libraries. Students have a $15 print allowance each semester and can add value with Dragon Dollar$. Users not affiliated with UIC can use a credit card at the printer to set up a Wepa account for printing .   About printing funds  About fees and Wepa   Wepa print stations are on all four floors to print, copy and scan. Flatbed scanners for books are located on the 2nd, 3rd and 4th floors. Scanning is free.  Accessible printers are available in the Daley Library (IDEA Commons) and in the Library of the Health Sciences, Chicago.  Public photocopiers/scanners are located in the Daley Library: in the IDEA Commons and 1st floor center west.  Library of the Health Sciences – Chicago  Wepa print stations are on the 1st and 2nd floor to print, copy and scan.  Public photocopiers/scanners are located in the Library of the Health Sciences on the Lower Level and 2nd floor north wall.  Photocopy Fees   Black-and-white copies: $0.10 per page for 8.5″ x 11″  Color copies: $0.50 per page for 8.5″ x 11″  Scanning: Free   More information about printing in Chicago   Peoria  A scanner is available to students, faculty, residents and staff in the Library Learning Lab. A public copier is also available with scan and send options.  More information about printing in Peoria   Rockford  Printing, copying and scanning are available to students, faculty, residents and staff using the Wepa print stations .  More information about printing in Rockford    Urbana  Printing is available to students, faculty and staff with a UIUC netID.  More information about printing in Urbana   UIC John Marshall Law School Library  UIC visitors will have access to a print station to print using the UIC Wēpa print system. This print station will be implemented in the Fall 2019 semester.          How Do I...?     Print (Chicago campus)    Print (Peoria campus)    Print (Rockford campus)    Get reproductions from Special Collections and University Archives    UIC John Marshall Law School Library - Frequently Asked Questions     Get More Help        Filter by Location    Chicago-Daley    Chicago-Health Sciences    Peoria-Health Sciences    Rockford-Health Sciences    Urbana-Health Sciences      Filter by Topic    Accessibility    Borrowing    Computers, Printing & Scanning    Copyright & Scholarly Publishing    Course Reserves    Electronic Resources    Library Accounts    Off-Campus Access    Requesting Materials    Research Help    Searching    Special Collections & University Archives    Study Spaces    Uncategorized    Writing, Style & Citations            Need help?  Contact a Librarian!                 Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations           Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Circulation  (312) 996-2724    Reference  (312) 996-2726    Special Collections & University Archives  (312) 996-2742    Course Reserves  (312) 996-2719                             Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago    1750 W. Polk St.   Chicago , IL  60612       Circulation  (312) 996-8966    Reference  (312) 996-9163    Special Collections & University Archives  (312) 996-8977    Course Reserves  (312) 996-8963                             Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria    One Illini Drive   Peoria , IL  61605       Phone  (309) 671-8490                        Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford    1601 Parkview Ave.   Rockf